gomodel:SYNGO_1755  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Fig. 5D and E, the double immunostaining showed colocalization of NrCAM (green) and Npn-2 (red) at numerous puncta (arrows) in confocal images of V1, layer 4 (P21) and dendritic spine puncta of pyramidal cells in V1, layer 4 (P21), labeled with EGFP by in utero electroporation and EGFP-positive, were labeled for both NrCAM and Npn2.\n\nLiteral:\n\"Double immunofluorescence staining showed colocalization of NrCAM and Npn-2 at numerous puncta in confocal images of mouse brain (P21) in sections of V1, layer 4, consistent with association studies in COS-7 cells (Fig. 5D). It was reported that Npn-2 colocalizes with PSD-95. In Figure 1C, NrCAM staining of puncta in V1, layer 4 (P21) overlapped with the postsynaptic marker PSD-95, while pyramidal cells labeled with EGFP by in utero electroporation showed punctate labeling at the tip of spines for both NrCAM and Npn2 (Fig. 5E).\n\n9/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Immunostaining is performed in mice brain electroporated in utero with EGFP cDNA.\n\nLiteral form M&M:\n\"Immunostaining and EGFP expression. Mice were anesthetized with 1.25% Avertin and transcardially perfused with 0.9% heparin saline, followed by 4% PFA in PBS, and brains were removed at E16.5, P21, P27, or P60.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1755" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

